  • Method Details

    • parseLRAGR

      public static LexRecord parseLRAGR​(java.lang.String pRow)
      parseLRAGR returns a lexRecord given a row from the LRAGR table This method leaves the key and number of tokens as null. The the key field requires the tokenizer, which is de-coupled from this class, and should be called separately. The number of tokens depends on the term being correctly tokenized, which should be done outside this class.
      Returns:
      LexRecord

    • toPipedString

      public java.lang.String toPipedString()
      toPipedString returns a pipe delimited string in the following format: term|eui|semanticType|extraStuff ... |tree if it is filled out where |-> extra stuff ---> |sab|sourceID|history|distance|tty|stt|reverseKey|numberEndsWith|tree
      Returns:
